cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the improvements in the 5G air interface and initial access in 5G NR, which are related to networking and internet architecture.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the unique features of directional access in 5G mmWave cellular systems, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as 5G NR is expected to support high-bandwidth multimedia applications, and the paper may discuss the impact of directional access on multimedia transmission.
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) is a less likely category, but still possible as 5G NR is expected to enable new AR/VR applications, and the paper may discuss the impact of directional access on AR/VR performance.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the system-level design principles behind 5G NR and the control mechanisms used to optimize directional access.
